	                            <span class="dsq-commenter-name">Victor Bocharsky</span>
	                        </div>

	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2722915078" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2722915078" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hey, Diego!</p><p>As for me, in this case I do "Replace in Path" (<code>shift+command+R</code> on any folder in project) for property name including dot in the beginning of it, i.e. <code>.type</code> =&gt; <code>.format</code>. For unique properties it helps a lot! But if property not unique, you could skip it during refactoring.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
